Here is a comprehensive breakdown of the frontend/UI conversation architecture in this codebase.

---

## 1. Sidebar Component (Conversation List)

The sidebar is **not a separate component file** - it is rendered inline inside `ChatPage` in `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/client/routes/chat-page.tsx` (lines 759-821).

Key structure:
```tsx
<aside className="conversation-sidebar">
  <button onClick={onNewConversation}>New conversation</button>

  {sidebar?.groups.map((group) => (
    <div className="sidebar-project-group">
      <div className="sidebar-project-header">...</div>
      <div className="sidebar-feature-activity">...</div>  // feature chips
      <ul className="sidebar-conversation-list">
        {group.conversations.map((conv) => (
          <button
            className={`sidebar-conversation-item${active ? " sidebar-conversation-item--active" : ""}`}
            onClick={() => onSelectConversation(conv.id)}
          />
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  ))}

  // "Unlinked" section for conversations not associated with any project
  {sidebar?.unlinked.map(...)}
</aside>
```

The sidebar is data-driven by `WorkspaceConversationSidebarResponse` which groups conversations by dominant project (via `touched_by` graph edges). Conversations are displayed under project headers with feature activity chips. Unlinked conversations get their own section.

---

## 2. Chat View Component Structure

The main chat UI is rendered in `ChatPage` (`chat-page.tsx`) using the `reachat` library:

```
ChatPage
  WorkspaceToolbar          // workspace name + seed toggle + pending file
  workspace-layout
    aside.conversation-sidebar     // sidebar (above)
    div.chat-main
      Chat (reachat)
        SessionMessagePanel
          SessionMessagesHeader    // "Workspace Chat + Extraction"
          SessionMessages          // renders each conversation turn
            SessionMessage x N    // each Q&A pair
          ChatSuggestions          // clickable follow-up suggestions
          onboarding-action-buttons  // "Looks good" / "I want to add more"
          ChatInput                // text input with @mentions and /commands
      aside.seed-panel             // toggleable live graph seed panel
```

Custom chat components registered in the `reachat` component catalog (`chat-component-catalog.tsx`):
- `EntityCard` - displays one extracted entity (kind, name, confidence, status, category badge, graph link)
- `ExtractionSummary` - batch entity display with relationship count
- `WorkItemSuggestion` - PM agent suggestion card with Accept/Dismiss
- `WorkItemSuggestionList` - batch suggestions with Accept All / Dismiss All

The `sessions` state holds a single `"main"` session with an array of `conversations` (each being a user question + assistant response pair). `reachat`'s `Session` / `Conversation` types are used directly.

---

## 3. New Conversation Creation

**From UI:** The `onNewConversation()` function (line 306) handles it purely client-side:
```ts
function onNewConversation() {
  setActiveConversationId(undefined);
  setBackendConversationId(undefined);
  setSessions([{ id: "main", conversations: [] }]);
  setSuggestions([]);
  setErrorMessage(undefined);
}
```
This resets the UI to a blank slate. No API call is made until the user sends the first message.

**First message creates the conversation:** In `onSendMessage()`, if `backendConversationId` is `undefined`, a new `conversationId = crypto.randomUUID()` is generated client-side and used when posting to `/api/chat/messages`. The server-side handler in `chat-ingress.ts` (line 41) does `const conversationId = parsed.data.conversationId ?? randomUUID()` and creates a new `conversation` record in SurrealDB on first message.

The newly created `conversationId` is returned in the `ChatMessageResponse` and stored as `backendConversationId`.

---

## 4. Client-Side Conversation Types/Interfaces

All shared types live in `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/shared/contracts.ts`:

```ts
// Single conversation entry in the sidebar
type ConversationSidebarItem = {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  updatedAt: string;
};

// Project group in sidebar (conversations linked to a project)
type ProjectConversationGroup = {
  projectId: string;
  projectName: string;
  conversations: ConversationSidebarItem[];
  featureActivity: ProjectFeatureActivity[];
};

// Full sidebar payload
type WorkspaceConversationSidebarResponse = {
  groups: ProjectConversationGroup[];
  unlinked: ConversationSidebarItem[];
};

// Loaded conversation with messages
type WorkspaceConversationResponse = {
  conversationId: string;
  messages: WorkspaceBootstrapMessage[];
};

// Individual message
type WorkspaceBootstrapMessage = {
  id: string;
  role: "user" | "assistant";
  text: string;
  createdAt: string;
  suggestions?: string[];
};

// Chat submission request
type ChatMessageRequest = {
  clientMessageId: string;
  workspaceId: string;
  conversationId?: string;   // absent = create new
  text: string;
  onboardingAction?: OnboardingAction;
};

// Chat submission response
type ChatMessageResponse = {
  messageId: string;
  userMessageId: string;
  conversationId: string;
  workspaceId: string;
  streamUrl: string;         // SSE URL for streaming response
};
```

Client local state also uses:
```ts
type WorkspaceState = {   // local only, not shared
  id: string;
  name: string;
  onboardingComplete: boolean;
  onboardingState: "active" | "summary_pending" | "complete";
  conversationId: string;
};
```

Zustand stores:
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/client/stores/workspace-state.ts` - stores the active `workspaceId` globally (used by chat component catalog for work-item accept calls)
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/client/stores/view-state.ts` - stores graph view state and `highlightMessageId` for cross-tab navigation (chat <-> graph)

---

## 5. API Routes for Conversation CRUD

Registered in `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/server/runtime/start-server.ts`:

| Method | Path | Handler | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|---------|
| `POST` | `/api/workspaces` | `handleCreateWorkspace` | Create workspace + initial conversation |
| `GET` | `/api/workspaces/:workspaceId/bootstrap` | `handleWorkspaceBootstrap` | Load workspace + active conversation messages + sidebar |
| `GET` | `/api/workspaces/:workspaceId/sidebar` | `handleWorkspaceSidebar` | Refresh conversation sidebar list |
| `GET` | `/api/workspaces/:workspaceId/conversations/:conversationId` | `handleWorkspaceConversation` | Load messages for a specific conversation |
| `POST` | `/api/chat/messages` | `handlePostChatMessage` | Send a message (creates conversation if new) |
| `GET` | `/api/chat/stream/:messageId` | `handleChatStream` | SSE stream for assistant response |

There is no `DELETE` or `PUT` for conversations - conversations are created implicitly on first message and never deleted or renamed through the API.

Implemented in:
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/server/workspace/workspace-routes.ts` - workspace/conversation read handlers
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/server/workspace/conversation-sidebar.ts` - sidebar builder with project grouping logic
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/server/chat/chat-ingress.ts` - message POST and SSE stream handler

---

## 6. Client-Side Routing

Defined in `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/boston/app/src/client/router.tsx` using `@tanstack/react-router`:

```ts
const rootRoute = createRootRoute({
  component: () => (
    <div className="app-shell">
      <header><h1>Brain</h1><ViewTabs /></header>
      <main><Outlet /></main>
    </div>
  ),
});

const chatRoute = createRoute({ path: "/", component: ChatPage });
const graphRoute = createRoute({ path: "/graph", component: GraphPage });
```

Two routes only:
- `/` renders `ChatPage` (chat + conversation sidebar)
- `/graph` renders `GraphPage` (knowledge graph visualization)

There are no per-conversation URL routes. All conversation state is managed in-memory in `ChatPage`'s local React state. The active workspace persists across browser sessions via `localStorage` under the key `brain.activeWorkspaceId`.

Cross-tab navigation between chat and graph uses the `useViewState` Zustand store: `navigateToChat(messageId)` sets `highlightMessageId`, which `ChatPage` uses to scroll to and briefly animate the message.

